0.1 Question , Dataset, Variables

  • My question is to find out if apparel consumption is driven by materialistic of hedonistic values, and how these values apply to the future purchase possibility of the product

0.2 Data

  • my dataset is underarmour data set

0.3 Variables

  • my variables will be categories of brand attitudes, UAIntent,environmental(for fills), knowledge1, materialism, physfit, prodaest, prodvalue, prodpur, online or retail

U_A.num <- U_A %>%
  mutate(brandatt = rowMeans(select(., contains('brandatt')), na.rm = TRUE))%>%
  mutate(materialism = rowMeans(select(., contains('materialism')), na.rm = TRUE))%>% 
  mutate(physfit = rowMeans(select(., contains('physfit')), na.rm = TRUE))%>%
  mutate(prodaest = rowMeans(select(., contains('Prodaest')), na.rm = TRUE))%>%
  mutate(prodvalue = rowMeans(select(., contains('Prodvalue')), na.rm = TRUE))%>%
  mutate(prodpur = rowMeans(select(., contains('prodpur')), na.rm = TRUE))%>%
  mutate(UAIntent = rowMeans(select(., contains('UAIntent')), na.rm = TRUE))%>%
  mutate(environment = rowMeans(select(., contains('environ')), na.rm = TRUE))%>%
  mutate(prodqual = rowMeans(select(., contains('prodqual')), na.rm = TRUE))%>% 
  mutate_if(is.numeric, round, 0)
mydata <- U_A.num %>% select(c("brandatt", "physfit","environment", "knowledge1", "prodaest", "prodvalue", "prodpur", "UAIntent", "prodqual", 'materialism'))

16 Comments

  • the null hypohthesis is there is no relationship between brand attitude and UAIntent
  • the alternative hypothesis is there is a relationship between brand attitude and UAIntent

  • since p-value is smaller than alpha 0.05, we reject the null hypothesis

  • the null hypohthesis is there is no relationship between physfit and UAIntent
  • the alternative hypothesis is there is a relationship between physfit and UAIntent

  • since p-value is bigger than alpha 0.05, we fail to reject the null hypothesis

  • the null hypohthesis is there is no relationship between materialism and UAIntent
  • the alternative hypothesis is there is a relationship between materialism and UAIntent

  • since p-value is bigger than alpha 0.05, we reject the null hypothesis

  • the null hypohthesis is there is no relationship between product value and UAIntent
  • the alternative hypothesis is there is a relationship between product value and UAIntent

  • since p-value is bigger than alpha 0.05, we reject the null hypothesis

17 Final Comments

  • materialistic values seems to affect female markets intention to purchase the product more than physical fittness

  • More knowledge about sports apparel leads more intention to purchase UA product

  • The female market is driven by both materialistic or hedonistic values pretty equally, however UA in general is being recongnized more as a hedonistic brand rather than materialistic

  • brand attitude also has a high correlation with purchasing intention of UA products.
